column10:
The game itself is extremely fun and the world building is breathtaking. It’s really easy to get immersed in the world, especially when you just go around for a fun little joyride. Overall, it’s a really beautiful game. To be honest though, just as a little heads up, getting the game to run was a pain in the ass. ;u; 

It seems like a common problem with the Steam version for some reason cause I found a lot of forums that were having the same issues I had. At first, the game wouldn’t even open, it would just appear running on Steam and through the task manager. And then, it suddenly crashed along with Steam. It took me several tries and redownloads to get it to run properly. Thankfully, it started to run when I uninstalled (with the amd utility cleanup on safe mode) and reinstalled my amd drivers. I made sure everything was updated before downloading it again as well. I also disabled overlay from other apps (i.e., discord and xbox game bar) for smoother fps.

I still highly recommend this game despite all the tweaking and troubleshooting I went through. If other new buyers face the same issues, I really hope you’re able to get it resolved and enjoy the game as well!! It’s a really fun and beautiful game.
